external_knowledge:
- The threshold of 5000 access events is used to filter out less accessed countries; 
- 'most frequent visits' refers to the total number of access events per country, as represented by the COUNT(a.access_id) in the query; 
- 'average daily COVID-19 cases' refers to the average number of daily reported cases, as represented by AVG(ct.daily_cases) in the query.

sql:
SELECT daily_cases
FROM case_trends
WHERE province_id = 1 AND date_reported = '2020-01-22';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT province_state) AS unique_provinces_with_high_cases
FROM covid_data
WHERE case_count > 1000;
